reviews.review_text: Good times Definitely the best show of the 3... best cover to cover show I had seen in quite a while and Jerry showed up for the whole thing. By the time night fell and space trailed off into Stella, I forgot all about the Safeway down the street getting completely overrun by heads. Mountainview really was THE BEST place to see a show. ( The gold flaked black pyramids weren't bad either... but that's a whole other story!! )

I agree This was the last worthy show I saw. .

The opening was stellar and it was steadily downhill till the end.

My Favorite 3 days EVER!!! The best 3 days I spent anywhere!!! After a long and winding journey from Philadelphia to San Francisco couped up with my best pal in a small blue Horizon we found ourselves facing a sea of beauty, friendly faces and sparkling ambiance backed by the wandering licks of Jerry, Bobby and the boys. Thanks for the memories!!!

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Set 1 HIGHlights: Big fun going on in the first set. I've heard better Eternitys but everything else is gold. 

Set 2 HIGHlights: Very respectable Help>Slip>Frank. Probably the best version of Shoe Fits I've heard thus far. First Smokestack Lightning of '94. DRUMS>SPACE IS A MUST-LISTEN FROM BEGINNING TO END. Wonderful Stella and Bobby songs on the outro.
